    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
            <ab>
                <lb n="1"/>
                <expan><abbr>D</abbr><ex>is</ex></expan>
                <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>anibus</ex></expan>.
                <lb n="2"/>
                <persName>
                    <name type="praenomen" key="Marcus">
                        <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>arcus</ex></expan>
                    </name>
                    <name type="gentilicium" key="Ulpius">Ulpius</name>
                    <name type="cognomen" key="Cerdo">Cerdo</name>
                </persName>
                <lb n="3"/>titulum posuit
                <persName>
                    <name type="gentilicium" key="Claudia">Claudiae</name>
                    <name type="cognomen" key="Tyche">Tycheni</name>
                </persName>,
                <lb n="4"/>coniugi
                <choice><corr>c</corr><sic>k</sic></choice>arissimae,
                <lb n="5"/>cum qua
                <expan><abbr>vix</abbr><ex>it</ex></expan> annos
                <num value="4">IV</num>,
                <expan><abbr>mens</abbr><ex>es</ex></expan>
                <num value="6">VI</num>,
                die<choice><corr>s</corr><sic><expan><abbr>b</abbr><ex>us</ex></expan></sic></choice>
                <num value="3">III</num>,
                <expan><abbr>hor</abbr><ex>as</ex></expan>
                <num value="10">X</num>.
                <lb n="6"/>in
                <expan><abbr>die</abbr><ex>m</ex></expan> mortis gratias maximas egi
                <lb n="7"/>
                apu<choice><corr>d</corr><sic>t</sic></choice> deos et
                apu<choice><corr>d</corr><sic>t</sic></choice> homines.
            </ab></div>
            
            <div type="translation">
            <p>To the divine shades. Marcus Ulpius Cerdo placed this epitaph for Claudia Tyche, his dearest wife, with whom he lived for 4 years, 6 months, 3 days, 10 hours. On the day of (my) death I gave great thanks in the presence of the gods and men.</p></div>

            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Line 5: annos (sarcophagus). The carver mistakenly changed from the ablative to the accusative (annis on the cippus), as indicated by the following ablative dieb(us).</p>
                <p>The epitaph inscribed on the third century sarcophagus is an eighteenth century copy of an epitaph on a second century CE cippus currently in the British Museum (acc. no. 1805,0703.204).</p>
                <p>Basis of verification: photograph</p></div>
            

